name="date-added">2024-04-25</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  Let <fr:tex>X</fr:tex> be a set and <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _0</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _1</fr:tex> two topologies on it.
  The topology <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _1</fr:tex> is said to be <fr:strong>finer</fr:strong> than <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _0</fr:tex> and
  <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _0</fr:tex> is said to be <fr:strong>coarser</fr:strong> than <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _1</fr:tex> if it is the case
  that
    <fr:tex>\mathcal {T} _0  \subseteq   \mathcal {T} _1.</fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks><fr:tree
