addr="jean-goubault-larrecq">Jean Goubault-Larrecq</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  Given a preordered set <fr:tex>(A,  \le )</fr:tex>, there are a couple of natural topologies
  on it to consider.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  The <fr:link
href="axt-003U.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-003U">Alexandroff topology</fr:link> is the <fr:link
href="axt-005U.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-005U">finest</fr:link> topology whose
  <fr:link
href="axt-0030.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0030">specialization preorder</fr:link> coincides with the order <fr:tex>\le</fr:tex>.
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
